the 68-year-old de laurentiis, who was a successful filmmaker in his native italy, also gave proxy to the company's board friday to vote his stock. he owns 60 percent of the los angeles company he founded in may 1986
for the nine months ended nov. 30, the company posted losses of $36.2 million on revenues of $46 million
