swaggart, a high-school dropout, is the cousin of singer jerry lee lewis. he and his wife, frances, have a son, donnie. in addition to the television ministry, swaggart has put out more than 50 gospel albums and runs one of the largest non-profit mail order merchandise businesses in the country. helicopters.</head>
thai and laotian officers today flew over a disputed border area to arrange for the disengagement of troops that had been locked in a bloody, 3{-month battle, a thai officer said
since a truce began friday, no fighting was reported in the area where hundreds of soldiers on both sides had died since fighting commenced in november around contested hills at the frontier
members of the laotian joint committee flew over the area in a soviet-made mi-8 helicopter while the thais inspected it from a u.s.-manufactured huey said thai army spokesman col. rithee rungkaputi
after the cease-fire began, two parallel rows of thai and laotian flags were staked to mark a zone which troops are forbidden to cross, said thai gen. charuay wongsayant
the fighting had been the bloodiest since communist forces triumphed in laos in 1975
gen. chaovalit yongchaiyuth, the thai army commander, said he would fly to the laotian capital of vientiane tuesday at the invitation of gen. sisavat keobounphan, the chief of the laotian army general staff
sisavat was chaovalit's counterpart at talks early last week in bangkok that produced the cease fire
thai and laotian military delegations agreed that their troops should be separated by 2 miles within 48 hours of the start of the truce
the affected area is between thailand's northern province of phitsanulok and laos' sayaboury province, an area about 240 miles north of bangkok
