the fire aboard the california zephyr was reported around 3 a.m. and was under control by 4:30 a.m., said fire chief jim mitera
it was unclear whether the fatality was a crew member or a passenger, mitera said. he said the injured apparently suffered either smoke inhalation or burns
passengers aboard the train saw thick smoke coming from the train, according to passenger vicki miller of omaha. the smoke appeared to be coming from crew cars just in front of the passenger sleeping cars, she said
police reported two cars were burning, said bryce wellnitz, a dispatcher with the nebraska state patrol in lincoln
amtrak crew members disconnected the two cars and the zephyr, which travels from chicago to oakland, calif., continued on its route
investigators did not know where the fire started or what may have caused it, mitera said
