moslems and jews both believe the site is the burial place of the biblical patriarchs abraham, isaac and jacob and three of their four wives
arabs spread prayer rugs on the floor and began to pray friday during jewish services in a chamber normally used at different hours as a place of worship by jews and arabs
the site attracts jewish and moslem religious fundamentalists and has been a constant source of friction since israel captured the west bank and gaza strip in the 1967 middle east war
