police across the country detained at least seven top opposition activists in an apparent effort to prevent a weekend solidarity meeting from convening, opposition spokesmen said today
among those reported held were two prominent figures in the outlawed trade union federation who were removed by officers from a car also carrying solidarity chairman lech walesa
walesa, interviewed by telephone from his home in gdansk, said union spokesman janusz onyszkiewicz and gdansk regional solidarity leader bogdan lis were taken from his car shortly after noon, but he was left alone
we have reforms by (means of) arresting,'' walesa said sarcastically. ``this is something well known to communist authorities.''
also reported held was zbigniew bujak, warsaw-region solidarity leader who was the union's underground chief after the imposition of martial law in december 1981
he was detained at the warsaw train station before he could board a train to gdansk to attend a meeting of the solidarity national executive commission, said the rev. henryk jankowski, an adviser to walesa
jankowski initially reported that solidarity adviser jacek kuron was detained at the same time. but warsaw opposition spokesmen said later that jankowski was mistaken and kuron had not been held
solidarity regional leaders from krakow, lublin, bydgoszcz and wroclaw also were reported detained
commission meetings are not announced in advance, and neither walesa nor jankowski would not state the reason for the meeting in the baltic port
however solidarity, which has remained active despite its being banned in 1982, is known to be evaluating its strategy in the face of steep price increases imposed feb. 1
the increases have caused widespread discontent, but no major unrest. past price increases have triggered violence as well as the strikes that spawned solidarity in august 1980
jankowski, who spoke by telephone from gdansk, said 19 people were detained nationwide, but there were contradictory reports from other opposition sources
a spokesman in the government press office, zbigniew augustynowicz, said he had no immediate comment on the reports but would look into them
authorities in poland often use brief detentions to block illegal meetings. since a 1986 amnesty, no one has been held more than 48 hours solely on political charges
wladyslaw frasyniuk, a regional leader of solidarity in the southwestern city of wroclaw, was detained friday evening by a group of uniformed and plainclothes police, said his wife, krystyna
police later telephoned their home and said without explanation that frasyniuk was being held for 48 hours, she said
it was not known if frasyniuk, who is also a member of solidarity's executive commission, had planned to attend the meeting in gdansk. however, he was to attend a meeting sunday of a banned farmers' group, rural solidarity, in southeastern poland
another executive commission member, stanislaw weglarz, was detained friday in his home city of lublin, in eastern poland, said opposition spokesman janusz winiarski
stefan jurczak, an executive commission member from near krakow, also was detained friday, another opposition source said
briefly detained was janusz stepniak, from near lublin, a leader of rural solidarity, said winiarski, who said stepniak was warned against attending the rural solidarity meeting in rzeszow
the provisional national council of rural solidarity, an farmers' union modeled on the soviet bloc's first and only independent labor federation, has called a national meeting of farmers to mark the seventh anniversary of the 1981 rzeszow-ustrzyki agreements
in those accords, the government officially recognized rural solidarity
after the imposition of martial law, rural solidarity was banned, although some members have continued their activities
