it's fantastic. you don't see too many parties like this any more,'' romero said of the friday night fund-raising bash that recaptured highlights of the seaside resort's history
hotelier larry lawrence lavishly decorated the venerable victorian hotel for 750 guests who came from across the country for a sold-out weekend at $2,500 apiece. money raised was going to some 40 charities
other celebrities at the gala included singers marilyn mccoo and billy davis and actors lloyd bridges, ed ames, jane withers, bernie kopell
